# Completion Review

- Auto-router fallback tail now has a structured ordered config, exact
  membership matching, AA/quality-gate exemptions, and allocation appends
  eligible routers after scored endpoints without consuming scored slots.
- Weekly tokens-per-request recalibration now has a transaction-scoped job that
  refines the global factor from calibration observations, recomputes only
  self-derived capacities, and is fired by its own scheduler cron under the
  daily run lock.
- Quota manager now assembles research, calibrated and live quota axes into
  request-equivalent daily binding capacity, converts live quota token totals
  and usage, and keeps effective remaining in the same normalized unit.
- Quota research now captures request and token axes from deterministic summaries,
  preserves both axes on active rules, routes sub-day request rates out as
  reactive gates, and applies the same routing to Instructor inspector claims.
- Quota unit normalization now has explicit OpenSpec deltas for quota-manager
  and telemetry-sync, binds conversion/config/token telemetry scenarios to
  executable tests, captures OmniRoute analytics token counts without fabricating
  missing values, and records future active-slice coverage in
  `tests/spec_coverage_pending.txt` plus `openspec/TODO.md`.
- Active implementation slices are archived: production pipeline composition,
  metadata persistence, apply-precondition derivation, and scheduler service
  entrypoint.
- Production CLI dispatch now composes repository-backed pipeline stages and
  diagnostics from validated startup config.
- Metadata sync output is persisted through the repository; dry-run validates
  without writes.
- Apply fails closed from repository guard state and exits 5 when DB/snapshot,
  desired state, quota safety, or probe/smoke evidence is missing or failing.
- `serve` owns the scheduler cron path and routes scheduled/manual/event/urgent
  triggers through persistent run locks.
- Scanner and free-registry persistence now write provider/account/catalog,
  endpoint, registry snapshot, and free-model rows through repository methods;
  source regression tests reject embedded table SQL in those stage modules.
- Production composition now dispatches `sync-free-registry` and
  `scan-providers` through registry/scanner adapters, removes the shared
  `_domain_stage_adapter` no-op, and requires explicit per-stage adapters for
  canonical domain stages at the adapter-backed boundary.
- Unwired canonical stages now fail closed with `not_implemented` (exit 3), and
  the executable effect harness rejects `success` results that lack a declared
  repository write, OmniRoute call, or idempotent no-change effect.
- All active OpenSpec implementation slices in this batch are archived; the
  executable scenario pending allowlist is empty.
- Production composition now wires `model-matching`, `quota-research`, and
  `access-classification` to their domain modules. Matching writes canonical
  endpoint bindings, quota research writes content-hashed summary snapshots and
  capped rules, and access classification writes canonical attribution status
  plus evidence. Missing quota payloads fail closed.
- Production composition now wires `probing`, `telemetry-sync`, and
  `quota-sync`. Probing is gated on confirmed access with remaining capacity and
  persists probe rows, telemetry sync writes normalized health observations, and
  quota sync writes live quota observations plus remaining-quota state.
- Production composition now wires `role-scoring`, `allocation`, and `diff`.
  Scoring persists per-role endpoint scores, allocation persists one planned
  combo target set per role with constraint reports, and diff persists minimal
  combo changes without mutating OmniRoute.
- Production composition now wires `apply` and `audit` end to end. Apply checks
  repository-backed preconditions, mutates only `fmo-` combos, runs the real
  smoke path without `/api/combos/test`, rolls back on smoke failure, and
  reports the real combo-test signal. Audit persists apply records and drift
  detection.
- Production composition now builds the shared Instructor runtime from
  OmniRoute `/v1` config and API key, selects only confirmed-free LLM models by
  AA `intelligence_index` with bootstrap/no-LLM fallback, routes quota research
  through the inspector with deterministic fallback, and records smart-combo
  advisory output without mutating deterministic diffs.
- Production composition now includes a `hermes-inventory` stage before
  `role-scoring`, uses the selected Hermes source adapter, persists inventory
  runs and role consumers, bootstraps new roles, runs the Inspector prompt-only,
  and lets allocation consume Hermes-derived `calls_per_run` demand.
- `aa-index` CLI commands now dispatch through the runtime handler. Analyze and
  proposal steps run `run_migration_agent` through the shared runtime, persist
  advisory threshold proposals, and deterministic approve/rollout/rollback
  paths own threshold activation and rollback.
- Production composition now runs role lifecycle reconciliation and demand
  forecasting before allocation. Allocation consumes persisted forecast demand,
  cold-start roles get a non-zero floor, and historical reserve is applied once
  before later forecasts use the base demand.
- Run-lock acquisition is now database-atomic through a partial unique index on
  active held lock rows; repository tests cover two independent connections,
  fresh schema installs, and migration installs.
- Code Simplifier review cleaned the new scheduler tests by sharing the partial
  index assertion and making concurrent-thread completion explicit.
- Apply stage now derives quota and probe safety from persisted endpoint state
  for desired `fmo-` combos. Missing, stale, non-hard-stop, or exhausted quota
  evidence and missing/stale/failing probes return `unsafe_to_apply` before any
  OmniRoute combo mutation.
- Code Simplifier review changed apply-stage safety queries to compare endpoint
  ids as text so malformed desired ids fail closed as missing evidence instead
  of raising a UUID cast error.
- Runtime documentation checks now allow only the explicitly named active-slice
  scenario pending list, and require those remaining slices to be visible in
  `openspec/TODO.md`.
- Hermes inventory now reads profile main model slots and raw auxiliary blocks
  from each profile's `config.yaml`, ignoring stale list-summary model values;
  Code Simplifier added an anchor on that source-of-truth boundary.
- Apply now rebalances only live `fmo-` combos from the OmniRoute combo set,
  skips absent desired combos as `unmanaged_combo`, and removes the unwired
  unknown-role immediate inventory trigger.
- Hermes inventory now emits non-auto profile and gateway auxiliary model slots
  as `auxiliary` consumers, and shared-combo demand sums those slot consumers.
- Quality gates now persist upper bounds, derive seed-anchored bands from live
  combo seeds, widen bands to forecast demand, and order combo members weakest
  eligible first.
- Profile normalization now rewrites raw or missing Hermes model slots to live
  `fmo-` combos by canonical model, falls back to the default profile combo,
  supports dry-run reporting, backs up configs before atomic writes, and is
  exposed through `normalize-profiles`; focused review fixed nested gateway
  auxiliary slot writes before commit.
- Quota research now runs only on reachable free-model changes, skips unchanged
  free-registry snapshots without `/v1/search`, uses OmniRoute `quotaTotal` as
  a limit hint during triggered full recalc, and deactivates lost-free models so
  rebalance drops them while provider-model rows remain additive. Focused review
  added the probe/quota safety stages to rebalance tests before apply.
- New confirmed-free provider models are now additively registered in OmniRoute
  through `POST /api/provider-models` only when their provider has an existing
  connection and no endpoint already exists; paid, unreachable, and already-known
  models are skipped, and an integration test covers registered models flowing
  through scan, matching, quota, probe, scoring, and combo rebalance.
- Multi-combo apply now persists each successful `applied` snapshot before
  moving to the next combo, restores the failed combo plus all earlier applied
  combos on later smoke failure, cleans rolled-back applied snapshots, and
  still attempts every restore before returning `rollback_failed`.
- Apply now compares the live combo baseline captured at apply time with the
  diff-time `before` state before mutating. Divergence returns
  `unsafe_to_apply` without overwriting manual/live changes, and rollback uses
  the live pre-mutation baseline.
- Top-level `rollback` now runs a dedicated combo revert path for `--run-id`,
  `--role`, or `--endpoint`, restores persisted `applied` snapshots to their
  pre-change combo state, records `rollback_reverted` audit entries, returns
  exit 7 on restore failure, and leaves `aa-index rollback` as the only AA
  threshold rollback path.
- Composition is now split into a thin root plus `composition_stages`,
  `aa_index_runtime`, and `composition_contracts`, with a structural test
  guarding the module boundary and the full suite passing without DB skips.
- Apply smoke now evaluates real OpenAI-compatible chat completion bodies:
  non-empty `choices[0].message.content` passes, empty content fails, and
  `OmniRouteRequestError` maps to rollback instead of a crash. Fabricated
  top-level `status_code` smoke fixtures are removed from production apply tests.
- CLI dry-run now executes selected pipeline stages instead of returning
  unconditional success. `apply --dry-run` runs guard/drift validation, reports
  unsafe gates, and skips combo mutation, smoke calls, and `/api/combos/test`.
- OmniRoute GET calls now retry bounded transient `502/503/504` and transport
  failures with per-attempt request ids. POST remains non-retriable and carries
  caller-supplied `Idempotency-Key`; apply combo writes pass their idempotency
  hash through that header.
- Production role scoring now applies context-window and quality-gate hard
  filters before weighted scoring, persists context/quality rejection reasons,
  surfaces endpoint rejection diagnostics, and skips new allocation plans while
  a role quality gate needs AA index recalibration.
- The canonical pipeline now includes a real `account-discovery` stage after
  candidate discovery and before quota/scoring inputs. `discover-accounts`
  dispatches to that stage, quota-pool membership and independence status are
  persisted, rate-limit failures stay conservative, and allocation uses
  account quota pools instead of double-counting same-pool accounts.
- Recorded slink fixtures now cover live OmniRoute combo rows and Hermes empty
  live state; formerly stub-heavy registration, composition, and role-lifecycle
  tests now replay recorded OmniRoute/Hermes bodies as their base inputs, with
  only scenario-specific overlays kept local to the test. Code Simplifier review
  cleaned the prompt assertion formatting before commit.
- Remaining deferred repo-level work: OmniRoute API bridge still returns 404 for
  `/api/combos*` on `127.0.0.1:20129`; tracked in `openspec/TODO.md`.
- No-auth quota calibration now resolves `opencode -> opencode-zen` as shared
  quota/model capacity, keeps alias misses and unknown no-auth providers
  inactive, and promotes only complete operator-observed OmniRoute token usage
  evidence.
- Hermes inventory trigger coverage now binds daily full inventory, explicit
  manual full inventory, and the unknown-role no-inventory/no-combo guard to
  executable scheduler tests; the matching pending allowlist entries are removed.
- Executable-spec pending coverage is empty again after binding the no-auth
  quota calibration scenarios.
- Fingerprint-backed provider connections now expand into deterministic
  per-fingerprint account scopes, persist stable account refs, parent metadata
  and `account-fingerprint` pool membership, fan scanner endpoints out to those
  virtual accounts, and remove the matching `account-discovery::*` pending
  coverage entries. Targeted tests cover fixture-backed pool multiplication,
  duplicate dedupe, missing-fingerprint shared fallback, scanner fanout,
  persistence, allocation, and the spec coverage gate.
